HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 249
BY REPRESENTATIVE FISHER
STUDENT/STANDARDS: Requests the State Board of Elementary and Secondary
Education to incorporate artificial intelligence into content standards
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the State Board of Elementary and Secondary Education to incorporate
3 artificial intelligence (AI) into content standards.
4 WHEREAS, AI is transforming every major sector of the economy and shaping the
5 future of work, civic life, and global competitiveness; preparing students for this new reality
6 requires that educators have both a foundational understanding of AI and access to
7 instructional resources that are age- and grade-appropriate and incorporated into academic
8 instruction in an intentional manner; and
9 WHEREAS, ensuring that exploration of AI is done in a safe, private, and ethical
10 way in schools is imperative; and
11 WHEREAS, the responsible integration of AI into K-12 education is essential to
12 building a future-ready workforce and ensuring Louisiana remains competitive in science,
13 technology, engineering, mathematics, and many other fields.
14 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
15 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the State Board of Elementary and
16 Secondary Education to incorporate artificial intelligence into content standards.
